## 1. Electrical Design Concept

- Provide a preliminary electrical planning structure for lighting, sockets, appliance zones, terrace/exterior equipment, smart home, and optional off-grid systems.
- Keep life-safety, wet-area, exterior, PV, battery, generator, grounding, bonding, and protection topics explicitly subject to licensed review.
- Use room-level YAML counts for sockets and light points as planning inputs only.

## 2. Grid Connection Assumptions

- Grid connection is assumed but not designed.
- Service capacity, metering, utility approval, earthing arrangement, main protective device, and point of connection are TBD.
- Any off-grid or hybrid system must be coordinated with the grid operator and licensed professionals.

## 3. Main Distribution Board Concept

- Main distribution board is assumed to be located in or near the technical room.
- Board sizing, enclosure rating, spare capacity, phase arrangement, labeling, heat dissipation, and accessibility are TBD.
- Segregate general lighting, socket circuits, wet-area circuits, technical systems, terrace/exterior loads, smart-home equipment, PV/battery/generator equipment, and future spare ways.

